other_tests.findings: Amorphous pink material throughout the superficial and reticular dermis with perivascular inflammation composed of a mixed cell infiltrate.
Presence of immunoglobulin G kappa monoclonal protein.
Mild immunoglobulin M elevation of 339 (normal range 48-271 mg/dL).
Normocellular marrow with maturing trilineage hematopoiesis; plasma cells not increased, no evidence of amyloid, abnormal myeloid maturation, or increased blast population.
Very minute clonal plasma cell population identified.

other_tests.procedure_name: Karyotyping and fluorescence in situ hybridization
other_tests.findings: Negative for deletion of RB1 on chromosome 13 at q14, monosomy 13, deletion of TP53 on chromosome 17 at p13.1, extra copies or amplification of 1q21 and rearrangements of FGFR3/GH, CONDV1/GH, and IGH/MAF.
